Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pop the @diced butternut squash{1%unit} onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the rigatoni.

When the water is boiling, add the @dried rigatoni{180%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until soft, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve ½ cup of pasta water, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, peel the @garlic{2%cloves}.

Roughly tear the @basil{10%grams} leaves.

Add the @cherry tomatoes{250%grams}, garlic cloves and half the torn basil to a large #oven dish{}.

Add 2 tbsp oil, 1 tsp salt and 1 tsp pepper (double all for 4p). Toss together.

Place the @Greek style cheese{100%grams} in the centre of the dish (keeping it whole) and bake in the oven for ~{12-15%minutes}, until the tomatoes are blistering.

== Dressing ==

While everything is cooking, make your dressing.

Halve the @lemon{1%unit}. Juice one half and cut the other half into wedges.

In a large #bowl{}, mix together 1 tbsp oil, 1 tsp lemon juice (double both for 4p), the @mustard{1%sachet} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Just before serving, toss the @salad leaves{40%grams} through the dressing.

== Assembly ==

Add the cooked and drained pasta to the oven dish.

Mix everything together, breaking up the cheese as you go.

Loosen with a splash of reserved pasta water if necessary.

Mix in the roasted butternut squash.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Dish up spoonfuls of cheesy pasta.

Garnish with the lemon wedges and remaining torn basil.

Serve the salad alongside.